Ext.data.JsonP['Using_the_Console_View']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Using the Console View</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-30083112\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Using the Console View</h1>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Chapters\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Chapters</span></h2>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Using_the_Console_View-section-src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Introduction\">Introduction</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Using_the_Console_View-section-src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Instructions\">Instructions</a>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Using_the_Console_View-section-src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-AddinganewlogmessagetotheConsoleView\">Adding a new log message to the Console View</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Using_the_Console_View-section-src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Addingotherlogmessages\">Adding other log messages</a>    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Using_the_Console_View-section-src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-RelatedTopics\">Related Topics</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Introduction\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Introduction</span></h2>\n    <p>Use the Console View (shown below) to find out the value of a variable or object at a given time. The value will be written out to the Console.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083112/ConsoleView.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083112/ConsoleView.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        </img></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Instructions\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Instructions</span></h2>\n    <p>This section describes how to do common logging tasks.    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-AddinganewlogmessagetotheConsoleView\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Adding a new log message to the Console View</span></h3>\n    <p>You will need to have the debugger set up to run to use the Console View. See <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Running_the_debugger\">Running the debugger</a> for help.    </p>\n    <p>To add a new log message to the Console View:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Open your file in the appropriate HTML or JavaScript Editor.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Navigate to the function or place in your code where you want to add the log message.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Add the following line of code to your code:    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">aptana.log(</code><code class=\"string\">&apos;&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">logMessage</code><code class=\"string\">&apos;&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">);</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p><i class=\" \">logMessage</i> should be the message that you want to be printed out to the Console View. (e.g.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">aptana.log(</code><code class=\"string\">&quot;Now is &quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> + tDate);</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">Debug</strong> button     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083112/IconDebug1.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083112/IconDebug1.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n to run/debug your code in your browser.    </img></p>\n</li></ol>    <p>The log entry that you added will print out to the Console View as it is executed.<br>Click the <strong class=\" \">Terminate</strong> button     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/30083112/IconTerminate.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/30083112/IconTerminate.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n to stop the execution of your code.    </img></br></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-Addingotherlogmessages\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Adding other log messages</span></h3>\n    <p><strong class=\" \">window.dump()</strong>    </p>\n    <p>In addition to aptana.log, you can also use <strong class=\" \">window.dump()</strong>, to print out to the console. The <strong class=\" \">window.dump()</strong> command is compatible with many currently popular JavaScript toolkits.    </p>\n    <p><strong class=\" \">aptana.trace()</strong>    </p>\n    <p>Use the <strong class=\" \">aptana.trace()</strong> command to generate a stack trace in the Console.    </p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083112_UsingtheConsoleView-RelatedTopics\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Related Topics</span></h2>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/About_the_Debug_perspective\">About the Debug perspective</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Installing_the_JavaScript_debugger\">Installing the JavaScript debugger</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Running_the_debugger\">Running the debugger</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Stepping_into_and_over_functions\">Stepping into and over functions</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Adding_a_breakpoint\">Adding a breakpoint</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=30083112\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Using the Console View"});